# Docker Networking in This Project

Although we did not create custom Docker networks, Docker networking was used during development.

## Functional Testing

We executed Newman using the host network:

```bash
docker run \
--network host \
postman/newman
```

Using `--network host` allowed Newman to access the application running locally at:

```
http://localhost:8080
```

This is an example of **Host Networking**.

---

## Docker Image Build

During image creation:

```text
Spring Boot Application

↓

Docker Image
```

Networking is not required because only the image is being built.

---

## Trivy Image Scan

Trivy scanned the Docker image directly.

No container-to-container networking was required.

